goals.question: What is the geographic distribution of incidents during the LA riots?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    gender_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange'])
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Gender')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(gender_counts.index, title='Gender')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(race_counts, labels=race_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the racial distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(race_counts.index, loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    incident_counts = data['type'].value_counts()
    ax = incident_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of incident types in the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Incident Type')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax.legend(incident_counts.index)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], c=data['type'].astype('category').cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Incident Types")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the geographic distribution of incidents during the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
